targetInputs.label: Electrocute Count
targetInputs.tooltip: Number of Electrocute casts to model. Total count will be spread evenly over the encounter duration with a randomized offset.

targetInputs.label: Include Frenzy
targetInputs.tooltip: Model the burn phase of the encounter with the stacking boss damage amp. Note that The Widow's Kiss will not be modeled even if this option is selected, since it is assumed that an off-tank will be pre-taunting to soak the debuff.

targetInputs.label: Tank swap for Decimation Blade
targetInputs.tooltip: If checked, the boss will be tanked by Tank 2 rather than the Main Tank during Decimation Blade windows.

targetInputs.label: Initial OT Blaze of Glory stacks
targetInputs.tooltip: If non-zero, Tank 2 will initiate the pull until the specified stack count is accumulated. Larger values allow the OT to gear more aggressively while still meeting the 250k HP threshold for the first Decimation Blade window, but make life more difficult for the MT during Inferno Blade windows. This input is ignored if tank swaps are disabled.

targetInputs.label: Initial Vital Spark ramp rate
targetInputs.tooltip: For the first minute of the pull, the simulated healing agent will accumulate this many Vital Spark stacks on average between Vital Flame refreshes on the tank.

targetInputs.label: Steady state Vital Spark accumulation rate
targetInputs.tooltip: Slower rate for the remainder of the pull.

targetInputs.label: Tank swap interval
targetInputs.tooltip: Elapsed time (in seconds) between simulated tank swaps

targetInputs.label: Add de-activation time
targetInputs.tooltip: Simulation time (in seconds) at which to disable Goriona's attacks

targetInputs.label: Burn phase HP %
targetInputs.tooltip: % of boss HP remaining when Goriona is de-activated

targetInputs.label: Nerf state
targetInputs.tooltip: Strength of the stacking Power of the Aspects debuff
